Definition: ostentatiously rich and superior in quality
Example: a princely sum; gilded dining rooms; these architecture magazines are full of the lush interiors of the rich and famous
Synonyms: gilded, grand, noun, attribute, grandness, luxurious, state, luxury, luxuriousness, opulent, opulence, princely, sumptuous, sumptuousness, sumptuosity, lush, lushness, ostentatiously, rich, and, superior, in, quality, a, sum, dining, rooms, these, architecture, magazines, are, full, of, the, interiors, famous
Category: adj.all
